Testing #34994

The following snippet reports a syntax error, complaining that there needs to be whitespace between `not` and `(`, [which doesn't seem to be necessary](https://drafts.csswg.org/css-conditional-3/#supports_negation).

```css
@supports not(display: flex) {

}
```

Testing #34994

```css
@supports (color: red)
{
	div {
		color: red;
	}
}
```

If you put your cursor right after `color:` in the supports clause, you won't get any meaningful intellisense. If you put it right before the `red`, it will work.

![peek 2017-09-26 12-38](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22350/30856112-a5f81e50-a2b7-11e7-9399-3a3a5b06fb7c.gif)

Testing #34993 

A workspace with

- main.ts file
- tsconfig.json with outDir: "./lib"
- no package.json
- compile TS file
- open .\lib\main.js
- generate launch.json. You get:

```ts
{
	// Use IntelliSense to learn about possible attributes.
	// Hover to view descriptions of existing attributes.
	// For more information, visit: https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=830387
	"version": "0.2.0",
	"configurations": [
		{
			"type": "node",
			"request": "launch",
			"name": "Launch Program",
			"program": "${file}",
			"outFiles": [
				"${workspaceFolder}/out/**/*.js"
			]
		}
	]
}
```

Observe: neither `program` not `outFiles` match any of my configuration.
